No matter how good you get, it still doesn't feel right being called an "artist". The term "artist" has been brought up to such a subjective standard. If one is hired to be an accountant, they are an accountant. If I am hired to make art, am I an artist? If one of Katie's followers here hired her to make a drawing because they liked her work, would that make her an artist as well? This video argues that she isn't.
